### REST Client for RPG-ToDo-App API Testing
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000
### Requirements: Start the backend server before running these requests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@contentType = application/json

### ==================== HEALTH CHECK ====================

### Check API Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health


### ==================== CREATE OPERATIONS ====================

### Create a new task
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Complete the quest",
  "xp": 100,
  "completed": false
}

###

### Create another task
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Defeat the boss",
  "xp": 500,
  "completed": false
}

###

### Create a completed task
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Collect treasures",
  "xp": 250,
  "completed": true
}


### ==================== READ OPERATIONS ====================

### Get all tasks
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks


### ==================== UPDATE OPERATIONS ====================

### Update a task (mark as completed)
### Replace {id} with an actual task ID from your database
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/{id}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "completed": true
}

###

### Update task title and XP
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/{id}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Updated quest title",
  "xp": 150
}

###

### Update all task fields
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/{id}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Epic adventure",
  "xp": 1000,
  "completed": true
}


### ==================== EXAMPLE WORKFLOW ====================

### Step 1: Create a test task
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Test task for workflow",
  "xp": 75,
  "completed": false
}

###

### Step 2: Get all tasks to verify creation
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks

###

### Step 3: Update the test task (replace {id} with the returned ID)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/{id}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "completed": true,
  "xp": 100
}
